               <msContents>
                  <summary>It is clear that the present text is scholastic, presenting a commentary on a literary passage; it is, however, unclear whether the commentary is on Homer (Il. 24, 753) or whether it is on Callimachus' Aitia, of which a section is quoted here (Callimachus, fr. 18, 8Pf. = P. Oxy. 2167, fr. 3).</summary>
